note.text:
Cystic Fibrosis DNA result: Positive for one pathogenic mutation: 3120+1G>A
      									Interpretation: This individual is heterozygous for the 3120+1G>A (c.2988+1G>A)
      									mutation in the CFTR gene. This result does not rule out the possibility
      									that this individual is affected with cystic fibrosis.  Clinical follow
      									up is recommended. Method: DNA isolated from dried blood spot specimen
      									undergoes CFTR mutation detection assay using Luminex xTAG Cystic Fibrosis
      									v2 (CF60) v.02. ACTION: SWEAT CHLORIDE TESTING AND GENETIC COUNSELING RECOMMENDED.

note.text:
Phenylketonuria (PKU) DNA Result: Positive for two pathogenic mutations: c.1222C>T/c.473G>A
                          Interpretation: This individual has two mutations, c.1222C>T and c.473G>A, in the PAH gene.
                          This result is consistent with the clinical diagnosis of Phenylketonuria.
                          Method: DNA isolated from dried blood spot specimen undergoes targeted gene sequencing
                          analysis. ACTION: REFERRAL TO METABOLIC SPECIALIST FOR DIAGNOSTIC TESTING.
